		<paragraph type="text" x="12" y="+16" width="280" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000" LETTERSPACING="0" KERNING="0">In 1970 there was a slight increase in both evening paper circulation and morning paper circulation. The <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[1]</FONT> rose by just over 1 million and the <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[2]</FONT> by almost 2 million. From 1980 to 1990 trends in circulation figures for evening papers and morning papers differed dramatically. Circulation for the <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[3]</FONT> fell by more than a third while for the <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[4]</FONT> it rose by more than a third. In 1999 circulation figures for Sunday papers and evening papers fell by 3 million and 11 million <FONT COLOR="#0000FF">[5]</FONT>.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
